HEADWORD: biovular
<hw>biovular</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>derived from two separate
fertilized ova; -- of twins; <as>as, fraternal twins are
<ex>biovular</ex></as>. Antonym of <ant>identical</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fraternal.</syn>⟦br⟧
